More importantly, there's some horrible code assumptions that prevent my name from being displayed correctly (the assumption being that two consecutive letters can't be capitalized). I filed a bug report months ago and what should be an insanely simple fix has yet to be deployed. Edit: Turns out that, after three months, instead of fixing the incorrect assumptions that went into their app regarding names, they did nothing. That's nuts. String manipulation is one of the simplest things to do, so their insistence that it's impossible to change really shows you how little thought goes into this app. I've cancelled my subscription because it's clear the money is not being reinvested in the app. Edit 2: There seems to be a serious disconnect between the PR replies to this review and the CSR with my support ticket. Great concept, almost. First, new users need this info: you will get people that like you right away, but you won't be able to see them. Just plan to pay $25 for a month subscription, then immediately cancel your subscription because it is auto-renewed. You will still get the 1 month full service but won't have to worry about additional charges later. Trust me, everyone in your area who likes you will do so within that first month. After a couple of weeks, the pool is empty. At least if you pay, you can see who liked you, like them back to make the match, and maybe have a chance for a date. Why is the pool empty after a couple weeks? Keep reading. There are range limits and time limits. Why in the information age do you want to place an upper limit on miles apart? What if I want to meet someone in another state, or overseas? Matchmaking should be smarter than geographic proximity, but in this app, it is not. Not local? No possible match. Sure, the woman makes first message, and that is great because it should disinterest the creepy dirtbags who spew phallic symbols without invitation. Problem is, matching is blind -> Unless you pay $. Still, if they don't msg me within 24 hours of matching (you both like each other's profile) then we are banned from seeing each other's profile ever again. So if she skips ONE day not bothering with bumble, match is gone forever. What if she travels? Works a long shift and sleeps in the next day? This app will only work for people who check at least daily like a ritual. If the match elapses, guy's left confused. Why if we both like and match, why no message? And so everyone is segregated after about 2 weeks. People who match are banned from ever seeing each other in the app after 24 hrs? I think that is stupid. I also think geographic limits are stupid. Match making could be more categorical. My 2cp, this app is almost good, just ok, and not bad compared to that other smut&smash app.

Here's my pros/cons at least as it relates to being a hetero guy using the dating portion of the app. Pros: + You get unlimited swipes on a free account + Girls have to message first so that's a pretty fresh change of pace that I enjoy + You get a good idea of the person's lifestyle through quick icon bio thing + Seems to be a little better for relationships than tinder if that's what you're going for Cons: - in general I've seemed to have a little more luck on tinder - it's not as picky with location settings so you'll match with girls like 60 miles away when you set max 30 Overall I'd say if more people used bumble than tinder it'd be the better app, but I still think if you have a tinder you should 100% also have a bumble.
